cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.CR

The paper proposes a novel learning framework that combines online ensemble algorithms and cost-sensitive bagging/boosting algorithms to deal with imbalanced data streams. This involves both machine learning (specifically, ensemble learning) and data mining (specifically, dealing with imbalanced data). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of image data sets, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and the need for security in data streams (cs.CR).
